other_tests.findings: Opening pressure was normal; CSF analysis: 815 RBCs/mm3, 14 WBCs/mm3 (43% neutrophils, 38% lymphocytes, 14% monocytes, 4% other mononuclear cells, 1% eosinophils), glucose concentration of 44 mg/dL (serum level, 116 mg/dL), and protein concentration of 69 mg/dL. VDRL testing of CSF was negative.
Pathological examinations showed necrotizing granulomas scattered diffusely throughout the prostatic tissue with yeast organisms consistent with H. capsulatum.
